history.content:
EE 16AB should be enough.

———————

I’m currently in 120 and there’s very little in the way of linear algebra or calculus! I would say CS70 is quite helpful in terms of developing mathematical maturity for 120, but not a requirement. 

------------------

Also a current 120 student; my experience is consistent with the above answers. Basically everything we've done (math wise) boils down to the idea of what linearity in a system means and the geometric series formula(s) from single variable calculus, as well as projections/inner projections which you see in 16AB. Haven't taken 70 yet and I don't feel like I'm missing anything by not having it, but I'm sure taking it before would help. You're ready for the class after the 16 series.
